Second Public Release of the OpenMAX core developed by Nokia and STMicroelectronics for Linux distributions

Major additions to the 0.2
- Component hierarchy architecture:
  - new base component
	- new one port derived component, for each source/sink component
	- new two ports components, for each encoder/decoder/filter
- The components of the 0.1 have been changed, based on new architecture. The components in the 0.2 delivery are:
  - Mp3 decoder
	- Alsa sink renderer
	- volume control
	- the reference component has been removed

